race.comment: KEEGAN'S REPORTS (2) is worth forgiving last start after finishing eighth (18.08) in a Grade 5 at this track over 300m. Cannot be left out. PETITE WHACKER (5) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when fifth at this track over 300m behind Rocky Bell (18.24) in a Grade 5. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from four attempts. Likely to play a prominent role. BOOTS AND ALL (1) was out of the money here last time out but can bounce back.
